    irrigationRegsPara: "Houston Public Works does not impose residential watering day restrictions outside declared drought, but the Harris County Water Smart program encourages efficient-use practices. Texas Commission on Environmental Quality (TCEQ) requires licensed irrigators (LI license) for any new system install. Backflow prevention (TCEQ Chapter 290) is mandatory. The City of Houston rebate program pays $50-$200 for WaterSense smart controllers. Woodlands Water District and MUD districts have separate conservation stages.",
